House Finance, Ways, and Means 1
Amendment No. 2 to HB1881
Hicks G
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1585* House Bill No. 1881
by deleting Section 2 and substituting:
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-2602(3)(C), is amended by
deleting subdivision (i) and substituting instead the following:
(i) Is zoned to attend a school in an LEA, excluding the achievement school
district (ASD), with:
(a) Four (4) or more schools identified as a priority or comprehensive
support and improvement school in 2022, as defined by the state's accountability
system pursuant to § 49-1-602;
(b) Five (5) or more schools identified as a priority or comprehensive
support and improvement school in 2023, as defined by the state's accountability
system pursuant to § 49-1-602; and
(c) Six (6) or more schools identified as a priority or comprehensive
support and improvement school in 2025, as defined by the state's accountability
system pursuant to § 49-1-602; or
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-2611(a), is amended by
deleting subdivisions (1), (2)(A)(iv), and (2)(A)(v).
SECTION 4. Section 1 of this act takes effect July 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring
it. All other sections of this act take effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it,
and apply to the 2026-2027 school year and each school year thereafter.
